43:55.107 --> 43:57.443
Okay, please hold.

43:58.711 --> 44:01.812
Hi Mrs. Mackie, this
is Bella Collins again.

44:01.814 --> 44:04.080
I was wondering
when I could come in

44:04.082 --> 44:05.749
to help finish my paperwork.

44:05.751 --> 44:07.518
The deadline's tomorrow.

44:07.520 --> 44:09.220
Call me when you
get this message.

44:09.222 --> 44:10.120
Thank you.

44:10.122 --> 44:10.956
Bye.

44:22.001 --> 44:22.836
Bell.

44:23.737 --> 44:25.339
Breakfast is ready.

44:27.507 --> 44:28.706
Bella!

44:28.708 --> 44:31.276
Stop yelling,
I'm right here.

44:31.278 --> 44:33.545
Come on, I don't
like cold pancakes.

44:33.547 --> 44:35.215
Sit down, let's eat.

44:38.852 --> 44:40.454
What, no interview?

44:42.055 --> 44:46.524
Hey, we're doing a story on
Danny's Bistro and cuisines.

44:46.526 --> 44:49.727
And we have some very
satisfyied customers here

44:49.729 --> 44:52.364
who'd like to share their
experience with you.

44:52.366 --> 44:56.536
Ma'am, what do you think
of la pancake a la carte?

44:59.072 --> 45:01.072
There seems to be
some sort of problem.

45:01.074 --> 45:03.241
Is everything okay?

45:03.243 --> 45:04.411
No, nothing.

45:06.212 --> 45:07.046
Okay.

45:09.750 --> 45:10.983
Is everything working out

45:10.985 --> 45:13.018
with that break you
caught at school?

45:13.020 --> 45:14.253
I don't know.

45:14.255 --> 45:16.489
That lady never
returns my calls.

45:16.491 --> 45:18.857
The deadline's tomorrow.

45:18.859 --> 45:19.694
Oh yeah.

45:21.429 --> 45:23.462
Okay look, you just eat up.

45:23.464 --> 45:25.498
Everything's gonna
work out just fine.

45:25.500 --> 45:27.300
How can you be so sure?

45:27.302 --> 45:31.404
You just eat your
la pancake a la carte.

45:31.406 --> 45:33.408
I'll figure out the rest.

45:36.477 --> 45:37.645
Go on, eat up.

45:42.783 --> 45:44.184
Come on, come on.

45:49.557 --> 45:51.459
Yes Shari, I'll hold.

45:53.628 --> 45:55.494
Hey Bella, anybody available?

45:55.496 --> 45:57.162
Tony in about five minutes.

45:57.164 --> 45:57.997
Okay cool.

45:57.999 --> 45:59.165
Can I help you?

45:59.167 --> 46:00.400
Yeah I know
you're pretty busy,

46:00.402 --> 46:01.335
but do you think you
could fit us in today?

46:01.337 --> 46:02.404
Yeah, sure.

46:03.539 --> 46:06.039
And if you don't mind,
while we're waiting,

46:06.041 --> 46:07.841
she has to go to the bathroom.

46:07.843 --> 46:09.809
Could you take her?

46:09.811 --> 46:12.981
- Hello princess.
- Alright sweetheart.

46:20.522 --> 46:21.988
Are you leaving soon?

46:21.990 --> 46:23.923
Yeah I have that
flight to Illinois.

46:23.925 --> 46:26.094
I haven't even packed yet.

46:27.228 --> 46:31.230
Bella Collins is
holding on line three.

46:32.901 --> 46:34.603
I'll call her back.

46:37.005 --> 46:38.204
You can say all
the junk you want

46:38.206 --> 46:40.206
about that pound for
pound but if Mayweather

46:40.208 --> 46:41.675
got in the ring
with Muhammad Ali,

46:41.677 --> 46:43.910
he'd get every pound
of that butt whooped.

46:43.912 --> 46:45.980
Man it's all
about the money too man.

46:45.982 --> 46:47.247
- Yeah.
- Hey.

46:47.249 --> 46:48.849
It's gonna take money
to pay the doctor bill.

46:48.851 --> 46:49.884
That's what it would do.

46:49.886 --> 46:50.951
Numbers don't lie.

46:50.953 --> 46:52.487
49 and oh.

46:52.489 --> 46:53.688
Yeah that's 'cause
Ali wasn't in there.

46:53.690 --> 46:55.358
Hey Bella, you okay?

46:56.859 --> 46:57.692
What's wrong with you?

46:57.694 --> 46:58.626
You alright?

46:58.628 --> 46:59.694
I'm sorry, what do you need?

46:59.696 --> 47:01.529
I'm about to go on my break.

47:01.531 --> 47:02.463
Check my 3:00.

47:02.465 --> 47:03.898
My 3:00 cancel?

47:03.900 --> 47:06.233
No, I need to leave
for a little bit.

47:06.235 --> 47:07.568
Will you cover the front for me?

47:07.570 --> 47:08.905
I'll tell Cliff.

47:09.772 --> 47:10.571
Yeah, no problem sweetie.

47:10.573 --> 47:11.406
Go ahead.

47:11.408 --> 47:12.640
Think he's out back.

47:12.642 --> 47:14.141
Bella been
acting weird today.

47:14.143 --> 47:15.776
Yeah, don't worry about Bella.

47:15.778 --> 47:17.445
You need to worry
about Mayweather.

47:17.447 --> 47:19.714
But listen don't get it wrong,
I like Mayweather too now.

47:19.716 --> 47:22.550
You would never
bet your money against Ali.

47:22.552 --> 47:25.622
It's not a
bad weird anyways.

48:01.892 --> 48:02.726
Next.

48:08.899 --> 48:10.233
What's the name?

48:12.335 --> 48:14.505
Sweetie, I need your name.

48:19.477 --> 48:20.578
Are you okay?

48:38.930 --> 48:40.229
You're missing your tax forms,

48:40.231 --> 48:42.634
your provisional certificate.

48:44.268 --> 48:45.103
Next.

48:47.271 --> 48:50.274
So we have a 211,
Clifford Bianco,

48:51.375 --> 48:53.442
discovered around 7:00 o'clock?

48:53.444 --> 48:55.077
It was
closer to 8:00 o'clock.

48:55.079 --> 48:56.915
And was it just you?

48:58.650 --> 49:00.550
No there were other
people in the building.

49:00.552 --> 49:03.119
But nobody that I don't trust.

49:03.121 --> 49:04.053
Nobody you don't trust.

49:04.055 --> 49:05.254
Okay, okay.

49:05.256 --> 49:06.055
So it was around
8:00 o'clock, okay.

49:06.057 --> 49:07.156
So you trust everybody.

49:07.158 --> 49:08.290
No, I trust everybody

49:08.292 --> 49:11.128
who was in the
building at that time.

49:11.130 --> 49:13.096
Okay so what exactly happened?

49:13.098 --> 49:15.298
Well we were in
here with some money

49:15.300 --> 49:17.701
and it was always
where it's always been

49:17.703 --> 49:20.137
and all of a sudden when I
came back around 8:00 o'clock

49:20.139 --> 49:22.239
it wasn't there anymore.

50:25.772 --> 50:27.205
Where is she?

50:27.207 --> 50:28.506
Is Bella here?

50:28.508 --> 50:29.741
No, she's at work.

50:29.743 --> 50:31.009
If you wanna talk to
her she'll be back soon.

50:31.011 --> 50:32.010
No, I don't wanna
talk to her Danny.

50:32.012 --> 50:33.578
I never even wanted to meet her.

50:33.580 --> 50:36.314
Why couldn't you just leave
things the way that they were?

50:36.316 --> 50:37.515
What was I supposed to do?

50:37.517 --> 50:40.484
Oh you
wanna play rescue now?

50:40.486 --> 50:42.120
- What's that mean?
- Are you a big hero?

50:42.122 --> 50:43.354
This is just like you.

50:43.356 --> 50:44.188
What?

50:44.190 --> 50:45.124
It's just like you.

50:45.126 --> 50:46.158
You know what I'm talking about.

50:46.160 --> 50:47.526
But it wasn't my fault.

50:47.528 --> 50:48.861
You can't keep
blaming me for this.

50:48.863 --> 50:49.695
Well I do.

50:49.697 --> 50:50.698
I blame you.

50:51.933 --> 50:53.265
Who left me for a poker game?

50:53.267 --> 50:55.534
Look, it was your first party.

50:55.536 --> 50:56.802
Nobody told you...
If you had just

50:56.804 --> 50:58.638
walked me home that night...
To leave.

50:58.640 --> 51:00.139
I never would've been raped.

51:00.141 --> 51:02.241
Kim, I'm sorry.

51:02.243 --> 51:04.877
I'm sorry this ever
happened to you.

51:04.879 --> 51:06.411
I've been trying to make
it up to you ever since.

51:06.413 --> 51:08.380
Well you can't.

51:08.382 --> 51:09.649
Well I thought the
least I could do...

51:09.651 --> 51:11.583
The least you could do
is stay out of my life.

51:11.585 --> 51:13.686
And leave the past in the past.

51:13.688 --> 51:16.055
And what about Bella?

51:16.057 --> 51:18.190
What about her?

51:18.192 --> 51:18.993
Ah Kim.

51:20.127 --> 51:21.160
Come on.

51:21.162 --> 51:21.963
Kim!

51:23.798 --> 51:24.766
Kim come on.

51:30.738 --> 51:32.973
I don't understand.

51:32.975 --> 51:35.942
You can come to me for anything.

51:35.944 --> 51:37.543
I know Cliff.

51:37.545 --> 51:39.047
I wasn't thinking.

51:40.015 --> 51:41.116
I'm so sorry.

51:46.121 --> 51:47.122
Come here.

51:50.425 --> 51:53.293
It's okay, I forgive you.

51:53.295 --> 51:55.729
Don't let it happen again.

51:55.731 --> 51:56.564
Okay?

51:58.033 --> 52:02.204
Remember, a thief and his
money will soon be parted.

52:03.171 --> 52:04.637
That's scripture.

52:04.639 --> 52:09.309
I believe it's
a fool and his money.

52:09.311 --> 52:12.679
I believe that's what I said.

52:12.681 --> 52:15.415
Wait, I didn't know
you went to church.

52:15.417 --> 52:16.783
How do you know scripture?

52:16.785 --> 52:19.953
Ah, I wasn't a
scoundrel my whole life.

52:19.955 --> 52:22.690
My mom put some
good things in me.

52:22.692 --> 52:25.827
Sounds like she
was a good mother.

52:25.829 --> 52:28.162
I wish I knew mine.

52:28.164 --> 52:30.564
She's the one
missing out baby girl.

52:35.171 --> 52:36.804
It's late, you should go.

52:36.806 --> 52:38.405
I'll have Bruno give
you a ride, okay?

52:38.407 --> 52:39.575
- Okay.
- Okay.

52:58.061 --> 52:59.961
Hey, it's you again.

52:59.963 --> 53:02.329
Danny, your money's
no good here anymore.

53:02.331 --> 53:03.798
What are you talking
about it's no good?

53:03.800 --> 53:05.800
It's green like
everybody else's, right?

53:05.802 --> 53:07.101
My money's good anywhere.

53:07.103 --> 53:08.569
Go home Danny.

53:08.571 --> 53:09.938
My order's not to let
you in another poker game

53:09.940 --> 53:11.508
in this town, okay?

53:12.542 --> 53:14.242
I guess you're right.

53:14.244 --> 53:15.610
I'll just play one
round and then we'll...

53:15.612 --> 53:17.412
Danny, go home.

53:17.414 --> 53:19.917
Have a good night buddy, okay?

53:25.555 --> 53:28.826
Come on
Uncle Danny, pick up.

53:31.328 --> 53:34.930
We both
know where he went.

53:34.932 --> 53:36.498
But he won't be
out late tonight.

53:36.500 --> 53:39.567
He won't be gambling
for a while.

53:39.569 --> 53:41.970
I just wish he'd
stop gambling.

53:41.972 --> 53:44.574
He has debt all over this city.

53:47.511 --> 53:50.745
Bruno, do you like living here?

53:50.747 --> 53:54.049
I've lived here my whole
life, for better of for worse.

53:54.051 --> 53:56.518
This is where I stay.

53:56.520 --> 53:58.187
Don't you
have any family?

53:58.189 --> 54:01.092
Nah, Mr. Cliff
is my only family.

54:02.861 --> 54:06.529
And if there's one thing you
need to know about family,

54:06.531 --> 54:08.898
we never steal from each other.

54:08.900 --> 54:09.968
You got that?

54:10.802 --> 54:11.968
Yes Bruno.

54:11.970 --> 54:12.804
I got it.

54:15.040 --> 54:19.142
Mr. Bruno, one day we'll
see more of the world.

54:19.144 --> 54:23.748
There is so much out there
that we haven't experienced.

54:24.749 --> 54:27.085
Here you go Bella.

54:28.286 --> 54:31.122
Tell Cliff I say
thanks for today.

54:33.724 --> 54:35.226
Will do.

56:18.498 --> 56:20.031
Bruno.

56:20.033 --> 56:21.333
Get over here.

56:21.335 --> 56:23.002
I'm at the shop.

56:23.004 --> 56:25.004
No, get over here right now.

56:25.006 --> 56:25.839
Okay.

56:53.734 --> 56:55.403
Here, have a seat.

57:00.975 --> 57:02.743
So, why are you here?

57:05.279 --> 57:07.513
It's so funny, I,

57:07.515 --> 57:10.519
I used to live in
this neighborhood.

57:11.653 --> 57:13.420
I used to love it here.

57:13.422 --> 57:15.688
All my friends were here
and we had all these dreams

57:15.690 --> 57:17.526
of changing the world.

57:20.129 --> 57:21.030
I do too.

57:22.164 --> 57:24.998
Getting into school
was my chance.

57:25.000 --> 57:27.000
I've been calling you for
the past couple of days

57:27.002 --> 57:28.801
about my paperwork.

57:28.803 --> 57:30.937
The deadline was yesterday.

57:30.939 --> 57:32.272
That was my chance.

57:32.274 --> 57:33.542
Oh Bella, I'm,

57:35.177 --> 57:38.578
let's see, there's something
I have to tell you.

57:38.580 --> 57:39.414
What?

57:42.851 --> 57:46.188
I had no idea who
you were a week ago.

57:48.390 --> 57:52.192
And when Clifford called
me, he described you as

57:52.194 --> 57:57.200
a teenage girl that he thought
of as like his own daughter.

57:58.601 --> 58:02.672
So of course I didn't hesitate
when he asked for my help.

58:04.174 --> 58:07.441
Because he saved
my life years ago.

58:07.443 --> 58:09.045
What do you mean?

58:13.349 --> 58:17.685
I was at a party and I
left the party by myself

58:17.687 --> 58:20.090
and something happened to me.

58:28.064 --> 58:30.664
Good morning, I'm
Detective Pollack.

58:30.666 --> 58:33.901
Are you the owner of this house?

58:33.903 --> 58:35.071
No, I'm not.

58:35.971 --> 58:37.505
Are you Bella Collins?

58:37.507 --> 58:39.039
Yes.

58:39.041 --> 58:43.179
We're investigating the
murder of Clifford Bianco.

58:44.848 --> 58:45.682
What?

58:46.817 --> 58:48.917
You mind if I come
in ma'am, for a second?

58:48.919 --> 58:49.753
Bella!

58:54.291 --> 58:55.459
Uncle Danny!

58:58.162 --> 58:59.163
Uncle Danny!

59:02.699 --> 59:03.700
Uncle Danny.

59:05.269 --> 59:07.068
Uncle Danny.

59:07.070 --> 59:08.071
Uncle Danny!

59:25.422 --> 59:26.590
How are you?

01:00:02.660 --> 01:00:04.927
Thank you very
much Mr. Collins.

01:00:04.929 --> 01:00:07.563
And as soon as you hear
or remember anything

01:00:07.565 --> 01:00:09.499
gimme a call.

01:00:09.501 --> 01:00:12.268
Also, I'm gonna need a
statement from Bella.

01:00:12.270 --> 01:00:14.870
She was the last one with
the victim before he died

01:00:14.872 --> 01:00:17.072
and well other
than Bruno Mercer.

01:00:17.074 --> 01:00:20.376
So at this point, she's
my only possible lead.

01:00:20.378 --> 01:00:21.345
I understand.

01:00:21.347 --> 01:00:23.180
If you just give her a minute,

01:00:23.182 --> 01:00:27.320
I'll bring her down and
she'll give her statement.

01:00:29.522 --> 01:00:31.054
It's all my fault.

01:00:31.056 --> 01:00:32.523
If I hadn't have
stolen Cliff's money

01:00:32.525 --> 01:00:34.691
he wouldn't have
been there so late.

01:00:34.693 --> 01:00:38.262
And Bruno would've been there
and he would still be alive.

01:00:38.264 --> 01:00:40.197
Bella you don't know that.

01:00:40.199 --> 01:00:42.699
And this is not your fault.

01:00:42.701 --> 01:00:46.002
Who's to say, Bruno
might not even be alive

01:00:46.004 --> 01:00:48.071
if you hadn't left when you did.

01:00:48.073 --> 01:00:50.941
Cliff is dead because of me.

01:00:50.943 --> 01:00:53.277
I've really messed up.

01:00:53.279 --> 01:00:55.448
I have to get out of here.

01:00:56.382 --> 01:00:57.781
It's okay Bella.

01:00:57.783 --> 01:00:58.617
It's okay.

01:01:07.092 --> 01:01:09.263
She couldn't answer any.

01:01:11.565 --> 01:01:13.066
I know who did it.

01:01:15.001 --> 01:01:17.201
I gotta get us outta
this neighborhood.

01:01:17.203 --> 01:01:18.035
What, you know?

01:01:18.037 --> 01:01:19.371
How?

01:01:19.373 --> 01:01:20.938
They came to collect
the debt I owed.

01:01:20.940 --> 01:01:22.840
Cliff tried to settle it.

01:01:22.842 --> 01:01:25.042
This was retaliation.

01:01:25.044 --> 01:01:29.614
You gotta
call the police.

01:01:29.616 --> 01:01:30.882
If you know who did this,

01:01:30.884 --> 01:01:32.183
why wouldn't they
just come back?

01:01:32.185 --> 01:01:33.117
You could be in danger,
she could be in danger.

01:01:33.119 --> 01:01:34.051
I mean come on.

01:01:34.053 --> 01:01:34.888
I know.

01:01:36.155 --> 01:01:36.990
I know.

01:01:38.492 --> 01:01:40.458
I'll handle it.

01:01:40.460 --> 01:01:41.659
I really don't understand

01:01:41.661 --> 01:01:42.760
why you wouldn't just
pack up and leave.

01:01:42.762 --> 01:01:43.728
Like you?

01:01:43.730 --> 01:01:45.565
Yeah, like me.

01:01:46.733 --> 01:01:48.400
It's not always so easy.

01:01:48.402 --> 01:01:50.101
Not everyone has
a place to run to.

01:01:50.103 --> 01:01:51.303
Yeah that's an excuse Danny.

01:01:51.305 --> 01:01:52.236
Come on, you could
get outta here

01:01:52.238 --> 01:01:53.905
if you really wanted to.

01:01:53.907 --> 01:01:56.509
You should get her outta here.

01:01:56.511 --> 01:01:58.513
Right, so you do care.

01:02:00.281 --> 01:02:01.447
Are you gonna tell her?

01:02:01.449 --> 01:02:04.283
I really don't
wanna deal with this.

01:02:04.285 --> 01:02:05.185
I gotta go.

01:02:46.194 --> 01:02:47.260
Bell!

01:02:47.262 --> 01:02:48.194
What?

01:02:48.196 --> 01:02:49.496
Something came for you?

01:02:49.498 --> 01:02:51.266
What is it?

01:02:52.501 --> 01:02:53.602
Open it up.

01:03:09.084 --> 01:03:11.084
Oh you did it girl.

01:03:11.086 --> 01:03:12.819
You did it.

01:03:12.821 --> 01:03:14.490
I'm so proud of you.

01:03:15.724 --> 01:03:19.060
Here, I have something
else for you too.

01:03:25.701 --> 01:03:27.133
Dearest Bella.

01:03:27.135 --> 01:03:29.636
I hope this letter will
answer some of your questions.

01:03:29.638 --> 01:03:32.640
I apologize if I frightened
you on my last visit,

01:03:32.642 --> 01:03:35.109
but I was trying to
find the right words.

01:03:35.111 --> 01:03:37.978
For years I ran from the
pain of being attacked.

01:03:37.980 --> 01:03:39.947
I thought my life was over.

01:03:39.949 --> 01:03:42.249
As a result I became pregnant.

01:03:42.251 --> 01:03:45.085
It was Cliff that talked me
into keeping the pregnancy.

01:03:45.087 --> 01:03:47.388
I knew my parents didn't
believe in abortions,

01:03:47.390 --> 01:03:48.689
so I didn't do it.

01:03:48.691 --> 01:03:50.891
Every time I felt the
baby move in my belly,

01:03:50.893 --> 01:03:52.893
I was reminded of that night.

01:03:52.895 --> 01:03:55.996
I detached myself
from the pregnancy,

01:03:55.998 --> 01:03:59.233
convincing myself I was
carrying it for someone else.

01:03:59.235 --> 01:04:01.869
I wanted nothing to
do with that night.

01:04:01.871 --> 01:04:04.539
I blamed my boyfriend
for it happening to me.

01:04:04.541 --> 01:04:05.940
I left.

01:04:05.942 --> 01:04:08.976
I left him, Cliff,
everything from that time,

01:04:08.978 --> 01:04:10.911
and yes, even you.

01:04:10.913 --> 01:04:12.346
I didn't think I could love you,

01:04:12.348 --> 01:04:14.482
but now I know I was wrong.

01:04:14.484 --> 01:04:16.951
To see you Bella,
makes my heart so glad

01:04:16.953 --> 01:04:18.653
that I didn't make the
mistake of denying you

01:04:18.655 --> 01:04:20.422
such a precious life.

01:04:20.424 --> 01:04:23.191
I don't expect you to
understand my decisions,

01:04:23.193 --> 01:04:26.928
but I do wanna be a part of
your life, if you allow me.

01:04:26.930 --> 01:04:29.397
It may take you
awhile to forgive me.

01:04:29.399 --> 01:04:32.133
I can only hope that one day
you will find it in your heart

01:04:32.135 --> 01:04:34.202
